name: ConditionalDataBarNegativeFormat
description: Represents a conditional format DataBar Format for the negative side of the data bar.

properties.name: borderColor
properties.description: HTML color code representing the color of the border line, of the form #RRGGBB (e.g. "FFA500") or as a named HTML color (e.g. "orange").

properties.name: matchPositiveBorderColor
properties.description: Boolean representation of whether or not the negative DataBar has the same border color as the positive DataBar.

properties.name: fillColor
properties.description: HTML color code representing the fill color, of the form #RRGGBB (e.g. "FFA500") or as a named HTML color (e.g. "orange").

properties.name: matchPositiveFillColor
properties.description: Boolean representation of whether or not the negative DataBar has the same fill color as the positive DataBar.
